items.description:
Agenda updated 2 Jan
======
Charlie to invite 3 new monPlan members as required
======

Agenda
1. Project Portal 5 min presentation from last year's Agile Lunch & Learn session
2. Agile Lunch & Learn sessions
3. Timelines, events and milestones
4. SAFe House of Lean
5. Agile Manifesto
6. SAFe Lean-Agile Principles
7. Agile for Teams
8. SAFe DevOps - CALMR & CI/CD
9. Agile Teams & other ART roles
10. 6 recommended practices for Continuous Deployment (CD)
11. Specifically focus on:
   > User stories
   > Acceptance criteria vs Definition of Done
   > Capacity planning (ACL)
   > Burn-up chart
   > Stand ups, retros, system demo
   > ROAM: Resolved - Owned - Accepted - Mitigated
   > Confidence vote

Separate coding session in the afternoon to cover refactoring and pair work

items.description:
Charlie to invite 3 new monPlan members
Agenda will be revised closer to the date
====
Hi Guys,

In this session, I'm bringing in a senior developer to run through good coding practices that we expect to see in the applications you develop, specifically in the Monash environment. Of course, you'll be able to take these practices and apply them beyond Monash.

We will be covering topics such as refactoring and pair work.

This is the first session and we intend to run for future student developers. Amongst the attendees here, we have student developers who are in the middle of projects, joined project mid-flight and some who would commence Jan 2018.

Make the most of it.

Kind regards,
Chau

items.description:
Dear Industry Partners,


My name is Surayez Rahman, I am the Industry Lead at WIRED Monash for 2018. Established in 2010, WIRED Monash is the principal student society for students in the Faculty of Information Technology and all those who share a curiosity about all things digital, regardless of their course.

 

We’re excited to announce that Industry Night is back again! This year, WIRED Monash is teaming up with the Faculty of Information Technology to present you the biggest technology-focused industry event at Monash University. We would like to extend the opportunity for you to come on board to witness our diverse student talent who are known to be innovative, creative and have a love of technology.

 

This year, we'll be hosting more students than we've ever had in previous years.

 

Here are some quick facts on IT Industry Night 2018:

•    IT Industry Night will be held at Monash University Clayton on the Wednesday the 21st of March 2018 from 6:00 pm - 8:30 pm.

•    The program will be open to over 3000 undergraduate and postgraduate IT students, from our Caulfield and Clayton campuses. 

•    The event will be completely free for all companies attending the event.

(See attachment)
  1. This is an optional event


- Dinner will be provided at 5pm (unconfirmed, TBA)

- Refreshments will also be provided 

- Setup time as well.

- Event starts at 6pm
